# AURAGAZE — Project Context

Mobile-first t-shirt ecommerce platform. Single Next.js app lives in `agz/`.
(The sibling `auragaze-frontend-revamp/` is a stale build cache — ignore it.)

## Source of truth for work
- Requirements: `docs/PRD.md`
- Sequencing: `docs/SPRINT_PLAN.md` (implement ONE sprint at a time)
- Decisions: see `decisions.mdc`

## Stack
- Next.js 16 (App Router, React 19, `reactCompiler: true`) — this is bleeding-edge;
  read `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before using unfamiliar APIs (see `AGENTS.md`).
- Prisma 6 + PostgreSQL (Docker, host port **5433**), NextAuth 4 (JWT, Credentials).
- Tailwind v4, framer-motion, lucide-react, sonner, next-themes.

## Current state (as of Sprint 2)
- Storefront catalog pages read DB products through `CatalogProvider` + product APIs.
- `src/lib/data.ts` remains only for category art/labels, shipping constants, and seed input.
- Auth is connected: register, login, logout, JWT session, protected profile/admin.
- DB schema now covers catalog, variants, cart, orders, inventory, addresses, wishlist.
- Seed (`prisma/seed.ts`) imports the mock catalog into the DB + creates an admin user.

## Conventions
- Storefront = mobile-first, `max-w-lg`, existing theme tokens. Prefer wiring real
  data over redesigning pages.
- Admin (future) = desktop-first sidebar layout; do NOT reuse the mobile floating nav.
- Money is in INR (₹). Free shipping threshold ₹4000, shipping fee ₹99.
- Don't scope-creep beyond the active sprint.
